On 11/12/03 5:09 PM, "Snoopy" <vwsnoopy(-at-)knology.net> wrote:


> And this connects to where???  Would it be the same for the 72-74
> exchangers?

It connects to the inner top hole of the heat exchanger/muffler flange and
one of the 8mm screws on the fan shroud. It is used on most years, including
72-74. It carries some of the weight of the exhaust system.

Scott Lyons
